§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The ❬trace❭ of a square real matrix is the sum of its
    diagonal entries. ⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the function which associates a matrix with its
    trace by $\tr: 𝗥^{n × n} → 𝗥$. ⦉

  ‖ The trace of $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ is
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \tr A = ∑_{i = 1}^{n} A_{ii}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Properties ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ¶ ⦊
    ‖ The trace is a linear function on the vector space of $n
      × n$ real matrices. ⦉
  ⦉

  <proof>
    ‖ Let $A, B ∈ 𝗥Mat{n}{n}$ and $α, β ∈ 𝗥$. ⦉

    ‖ Define $C = α A + β B$. ⦉

    ‖ Then $C_{ii} = α A_{ii} + β B_{ii}$. ⦉

    ‖ So
      ◇ ⦊
        ‖ \begin{aligned} ⦉

        ‖ \tr C = ∑_{i = 1}^{n} C_{ii} ⦉

        ‖ ❲&❳= ∑_{i = 1}^{n} α A_{ii} + β B_{ii} ᜶ ⦉

        ‖ ❲&❳= α ∑_{i = 1}^{n} A_{ii} + β ∑_{i = 1}^{n} B_{ii}
          ᜶ ⦉

        ‖ ❲&❳= α \tr A + β \tr B. ⦉

        ‖ \end{aligned} ⦉
      ⦉⦉
  </proof>
</statement>
<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $A, B ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$. Then
    ◇ ⦊
      ‖ \trp{AB} = \trp{BA}. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ In other words, “matrices commute under the trace operator.” ⦉
⦉

<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ Let $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$. Then $\tr A = \tr A^⊤$. ⦉
</statement>
